Requirement 1
-A piece can be placed on any empty space of a 3×3 board.
test 1=
When a piece is placed anywhere outside the X axis, then RuntimeException
is thrown.
test2 =
When a piece is placed anywhere outside the Y axis, then RuntimeException
is thrown.
test3
When a piece is placed on an occupied space, then RuntimeException is
thrown.

Requirement 2
Now it's time to work on the speciication of which player is about to play his turn.
We can split this requirement into three tests:
• The first turn should be played by played X
• If the last turn was played by X , then the next turn should be played by O
• If the last turn was played by O , then the next turn should be played by X

Requirement 3
A player wins by being the first to connect a line of friendly
pieces from one side or corner of the board to the other.
If no winning condition is fulilled, then there is no winner.
